-Absor<br>
<br>
Just wanted to bring up a point. The same thing could be said about wizards being 3 person damage dealers. A wizard needs a tank as well and someone to heal that tank in order to deal damage without getting killed (unless they are kiting). So you wouldn't have to &quot;divide by three, then compare&quot;. <p><img src=http://shadoworder.cjb.net/sigs/Ybik-sig5c.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 10:13:01 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Absor's post</span><hr size=1> They might come up with, &quot;Well at least they have the soloing ability that tanks don't have.&quot;  In a group related game, I somehow don't see the novelty that others do.<br>
