wave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 9:01:07 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Absor's post</span><hr size=1> To max out a Wizard's effectiveness (just as a Rogue requires the tank/cleric and Enchanter to max out their effectiveness), we need a tank, healer, enchanter, bard and a debuffer such as a Magician, Necromancer, Shaman, or even Druid for fire spells.  In other words, to max out a Rogue, you need 4 people.  To max out a Wizard you need a full group.  Of course there are always going to be people who say side issues like &quot;d00d I can kite Raptorz!!!1!&quot; and &quot;I did a monster in Guk with just me and a ranger!!&quot; which totally ignores the argument. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 9:16:44 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/NEW4.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span